\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14483652 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 Do you remember Mrs Cullis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15352313 JE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 Yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14483652 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15352313 JE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086728\charrsid6557717 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 
 Cullis was a rough diamond. She - her father - was nicknamed - John Garabaldi, and that is very interesting, because - people called him John Garabaldi but Mrs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086728\charrsid6557717 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717  Cullis would stand up for him and say that that was - his greatest hour - of glory. It appears that there was a hurricane blowing, over the old - iron works one night, and that - qu
ite a lot of damage had been done, and many of the men had - gone for shelter, but John Cullis had stood his ground, braved the storm and the following morning when it was over and the - manager of the works came, and having known what had happened, he sa
id at the time, even Garibaldi wouldn't have done anything braver, and that was why he was called John Baribaldi.
\par 
