s in Carmarthen was the church at the time, and Gyfylchi was an old chapel of ease on top of the mountain, that came within that five mile law. The farers came, even as far as Pencoed and Llangan to the communion service at Gyfylchi, but the
y - it went too small and the first one they came to Taibach, and we read that the Hickocks of Taibach - were the - founders of the community that founded a branch of Gyfylchi in Taibach. Later - William Thomas, another farmer from Pyle in 1811 - he gave 
a plot of land that Capel y Pil as we know it today in Pyle, so that was the - or the circuit, Gyfylchi in the morning, Dyffryn Taibach in the afternoon, and Capel y pil in the evening.
