hey had to do the housework, some of them even had to do the weeks washing. I know - my friend - he was living across the river, he couldn't afford any work on Sunday, he had the washing to do. And I've seen him many times - with a canvas apron in front o
f him, and the old rhuba then over a tub, that would be rubbing the clothes and he would see them all out.
