day school - with - she never told us children - to go to Sunday school, it was always - now come. And she would be leading. My father being a colliery official - meant that he very - he had to do quite a lot of - Sunday morning work, reports and so forth
. But apart from that my mother kept the family - and she would be - very near as often as we would be - in the service.
