a
fts, not the two pit shafts, but the two gage - the up and down cages And my job was to - regulate these trams, that one would got the - left and one would go to the right, and if that - there were sufficient trams on the track to stop the creeper. Which 
w
as called the creeper boy. Well the next step afterwards was to - graduate down to the pit bottom, where it was - to - couple up, chutler, to couple up these trams, ready for the horse to take them away. But one side of the colliery - the air was going on
e side and I had to stop the air going to another, which meant that there were three - brattis doors, they were wooden doors - that were airtight, and you had to keep these always airtight. So - there was another - distinction to become a door}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 boy. And the door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 
y used to go in front of the horse, and he would open one and - the driver would come and - the horse would come along and he - would close the door after, and to - these three doors. Well - the - the difference in the creeper boy - that was - two a
nd six a day. Two and six a day was the starting - but when I went down to the pit bottom that became three and four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 
pence. And then - it became - six and eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 pence, it was such a heavy job, the shuttling job was six and eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6450268\charrsid6557717  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 pence. And of course that I
 - owe much to my physique for these kind of jobs, because the pit - the timber was coming down the pit in the cage and very young I had to acquaint myself to carrying - pit props, six and a half feet, from the pit cage and to put them in these trams to g
o away.
