Yes, I started in - in 1916. And then - I was very happy in the various - I graduated from there, at seventeen - I - I had a stall of my own, because I said I was eighteen. Well as a collier, as one had wo
rked that year, well I had a stall on my own at seventeen - and - I was very very good, we had to - it was on condition - that you paid the way, they didn't want the ones that were on the minimum wage, you see, you were expected - you were expected to - t
o pay your way, unless there were - circumstances sometime the - the coal would go - the seam would go against you, and -
