ain deep - but something happened - my brother and I were working together at the time, it was just at that time that he - had been appointed as an adjuster of weights and measures for the Glamorgan County council - and of course - it was on the - conditi
on that he passed the inspect}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid949540\charrsid6557717 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 
rate in three years. Well having lost my brother, and I knew at that time - that I had been working - in front of the air, because as you were advancing in the deep you were in front of the air all the time, and there was - and
 I suffer for it today you can hear my chest wheezing now and then, that's what happened, but I could see that it was coming off then. So - I - went back to - to the heading from the main deep I went back to the heading, and to do some contract repairing.
 
Contract repairing meant that you would - agree - to do the job - for - a certain price, which was very good. Well - the 1926 strike came, and we were - went back - on worse terms, but the - thing that I can remember afterwards - were that - the collier -
 the - the coal owners then were - harder masters. And it was in 19 - about 1928 that they introduced mechanical mining - to our colliery, and I'll never forget, I was chosen to be one of a gang of \{ILLEGIBLE\}
