's - public work engineer's - Constable and Hart, behind the concret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid949540\charrsid6557717 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid489342\charrsid6557717 
 mix - mixer, road working, road making, and - there it was very heavy work but it was - very good, I think it was one and ten an hour we used to have at the time, but it brought us more t
han three pound five a week which was a good wage when the minimum wage in the colliery at that time - was two pound five. But those jobs were coming to an end very quick, when you come to the length, to the end of the length - you were given a card and d
i
scharged, and it was then - that I - got acquainted with the - people who were working on the parks and open spaces at Harrow. And - having seen the - engineer - was employed - first of all as a labourer on the London Parks, very soon I graduated to be a 
